  "text": "The Lifeways study is a prospective cohort study which was established between 2001 and 2003. A total of 1,124 pregnant women from 2 maternity hospitals in Ireland were recruited at the time of their first ante-natal visit [CITATION_1] . At this visit, a midwife invited Irish-born mothers to participate and, following the provision of informed consent, the women completed a questionnaire relating to general health, lifestyle, diet and socio-demographic characteristics. Partners were invited to participate in the study by the women who consented and provided their partner's contact details. The partners completed a similar questionnaire following the ante-natal visit.",
